          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Deuterated polyethylene (CD2) n target of thickness",
                "400 mg/cm2"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Sample is located in large-bore, uniform-",
                "field magnetic superconducting solenoid with",
                "adjustable B= 2-5 T. Light charged particles emitted",
                "in reaction are transported in solenoidal field to",
                "upstream and downstream Si array."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Charged particles are detected using a hollow",
                "array of 24 silicon detectors that is placed on the",
                "solenoid axis. The detectors are position sensitive",
                "in the longitudinal direction. The silicon detectors",
                "measure the particle's energy, distance from the",
                "target, and flight time"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SI",
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A group of silicon dE-E telescopes were",
                "placed at Z = 42 cm to identify the 9-11Be reaction",
                "products. The thicknesses of the dE and E silicon",
                "detectors were 75mu-m and 1000 mu-m, respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE",
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Coincidence between light particles in",
                "in Si array and 11Be,10Be ions in recoil detectors",
                "was required for reaction identification."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The 12 MeV/u 12B secondary beam was produced using",
                "the neutron adding reaction on a 11B primary beam at",
                "13.5 MeV/u. Primary 11B beam bombarded A 3.7cm-long D2",
                "gas cell at a pressure of 1400 mbar and temperature",
                "of 90 K. The resulting 12B was selected in momentum",
                "by the beamline dipole magnets. Beam rate was",
                "approximately 2E+5 particles/sec and less than 5%",
                "contamination."
              ]
            }
          ],
